    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-06-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="233" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                <head>No. 233.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Davis</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-06-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 26,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 617.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to previous correspondence on
                        the subject, I inclose herewith for your information a copy of a dispatch
                        from Mr. Wallace, the American minister at Constantinople,<note n="*" xml:id="d233fn1">See Mr. Wallace to Mr. Frelinghuysen, No. 226, June 4,
                            1883, <hi rend="italic">post.</hi>
                    </note> reporting the action taken by
                        the Italian, French and Austrian Governments with reference to religious
                        intolerance in Bulgaria.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN DAVIS,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Sscretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
